The paper deals with texture analysis on 3D surfaces, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The Local Binary Pattern (LBP) is a well-known technique in computer vision, and the paper introduces an extension of it for 3D surfaces, which could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also deals with pattern retrieval and classification, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
